@pb-cdunn, I believe to know the reason for the deadlocking already. As it says in the [patch](https://github.com/spotify/luigi/pull/1427/files#diff-f1cd3288d80ac94f428311dbefa70c7fR1169): Pool-processes are stuck on `put()` since nobody is reading on the other end. And main thread doesn't quit because it waits for the pool-processes to join (exit).

Then I noticed that it is still "getting stuck" on Ctrl+C despite changing `pool.join()` to `pool.terminate()`, so my theory might very well be wrong.

