* i didn't file a bug, but [fix](https://github.com/google/apitools/commit/a6feb8a17c6d9e8735d878c1935f489604f2b953) is in `master` on apitools. (reviewed internally -- just about at the point where i don't have to do that anymore. :grinning: )

* so [httplib.HTTPConnection.request](https://github.com/google/apitools/commit/a6feb8a17c6d9e8735d878c1935f489604f2b953) allows `body` to be a file-like object, and (in that case) will read all contents from the stream. i think the right approach here is to exhaust `body` in the [`request` method](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python/blob/41b5b722305e8aaba09442bd70c16c595c55a63b/gcloud/storage/test_blob.py#L1055) -- but i don't know if that's the only hiccup you'll hit. in particular, though, doing something like

        def request(self, uri, method, headers, body, **kw):
            if hasattr(body, 'read'):
                body = body.read()
            return self._respond(uri=uri, method=method, headers=headers,
                                 body=body, **kw)

  leads to this test passing (since we're now actually reading the bytes from the upload stream).

