@ankurankan Okay. Here is what I have planned.
I will add the functionality to store the state names in the base classes i.e. ```UndirectedGraph``` and ```DirectedGraph``` as a dictionary attribute, with nodes as keys and a list of state names for each node as values. Mapping would be the index number of each state name in the state names list for each key in the dictionary attribute.
Now, I will write a separate decorator for each method that involves work with state names. For cases when the state names are not provided, the decorators will simply return the original method, thus retaining the previous behavior. All the code involving state names would be kept in the decorators, thus keeping the previous classes unchanged.

