@nkeim I think we are on the same line of thoughts. So trackpy puts the origin of the pixel at the *center* of the topleft pixel? I would call that position (0.5, 0.5). I never realized this. It should be somewhere in the docs.

Currently, the sampling is done at the topleft of every pixel. This should be adapted using 0.5 at some places then. Ideally there should be a (weighted) average indeed. For the general feature profile, you could do that numerically by generating a much finer grid of pixels and then average. But that is a future extension.

About the 0.2 mistake, I think this is because of the `- 1` in the (continuous) artificial feature **and** because in `test_rg` the background is chosen using `np.ones` instead of `np.zeros`. This background will increase the Rg. If I adapt these two things, the `0.2` is gone and values agree within 0-3% depending on subpx position of the feature.

