@andymoe here's what worked for me (beware--it's ugly!)

`network application-gateway update -g rg -n ag --set backendHttpSettingsCollection[0].probe={\"id\":\"/subscriptions/****/resourceGroups/rg/providers/Microsoft.Network/applicationGateways/ag/probes/probe1\"}`

Within the CLI, the object updates properly, but then when msrest tries to serialize it, it chokes. I think it is because the `probe` property of the `backend_http_settings_collection` is listed as a "SubResource" rather than a "Probe", but that will let you set the probe. Whether that unblocks your scenario or not I'd be curious to know, but I already plan on adding proper arguments to update these kinds of properties, and will likely allow creation of the probe at the same time as the gateway.

