@jackiekazil By comparing results with the basic algorithm below, I'm sure that the get_distance method in mesa 0.77 is the only right one by now.

```
def code_for_basic(center, size, torus, pos_1, pos_2):
    if not torus:
        return np.linalg.norm(pos_1 - pos_2)
    else:
        distance_list = np.zeros(9)
        for i in range(3):
            for j in range(3):
                pos_1_temp = pos_1 + np.array(((i-1) * size[0], (j-1) * size[1]))
                distance_list[i*3+j] = np.linalg.norm(pos_1_temp - pos_2)
        return distance_list.min()
```

